%%{init: {'theme': 'default', 'sequence': {'actorFontSize': 22, 'actorFontWeight': 'bold', 'messageFontSize': 20, 'noteFontSize': 18, 'mirrorActors': false, 'actorMargin': 60, 'boxMargin': 12, 'messageMargin': 40, 'wrap': true}}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    actor Admin as Sys Admin

    participant AUI as ram-admin-ui
    participant Authz as ram-authorisation
    participant Ref as ram-reference-data
    participant DB as Shared schema
    participant OtherSvc as Any other ram service

    rect rgb(232, 240, 250)
        Note over Admin,OtherSvc: Phase 1 — Admin login and role-gate
        Admin->>AUI: open admin.ram.hmcts.gov.uk
        AUI->>Authz: OIDC and POST /authz/check requiring sys-admin role
        Authz-->>AUI: sys-admin allowed, or 403 for non-admin users
        AUI-->>Admin: admin-scoped Home with Reference Data and User & Role nav
    end

    rect rgb(232, 250, 232)
        Note over Admin,OtherSvc: Phase 2 — Path A — Reference Data write per FR6
        Note right of Admin: Same flow for any of the 15 Reference Data tables — Regions, Offices, calendar / FY, 12 judicial vocabularies.
        Admin->>AUI: edit a Reference Data entry and submit
        AUI->>Ref: POST /v1/reference-data/{table} or PUT for update
        Ref->>Ref: validate and record named-owner sign-off per FR6
        Ref->>DB: persist row to the owning Reference Data table
        Ref-->>AUI: 201 or 200
        AUI-->>Admin: confirmation toast
    end

    rect rgb(250, 240, 230)
        Note over Admin,OtherSvc: Phase 3 — Path B — User & Role write per FR4
        Note right of Admin: Affects any of the 5 auth tables — ram_auth_users, ram_auth_roles, ram_auth_user_roles, ram_auth_user_region_scopes, ram_auth_user_activation_flags.
        Admin->>AUI: edit user role or Region/Area scope and submit
        AUI->>Authz: POST /v1/users or PUT /v1/users/{id}/roles
        Authz->>Authz: validate. ram-authorisation is both gatekeeper and writer here
        Authz->>DB: persist row to the owning auth table
        Authz-->>AUI: 201 or 200
        AUI-->>Admin: confirmation toast
    end

    rect rgb(250, 232, 240)
        Note over Admin,OtherSvc: Phase 4 — Downstream visibility, no propagation step
        Note right of OtherSvc: No cache, no event bus, no propagation. The next consumer call picks up the change naturally.
        OtherSvc->>DB: direct SQL read of Reference Data on next request that needs it
        DB-->>OtherSvc: includes the new or updated row
        OtherSvc->>Authz: POST /authz/check for the affected user on their next request
        Authz->>DB: read updated auth tables
        DB-->>Authz: returns updated roles, scope, activation
        Authz-->>OtherSvc: new effective permissions
    end

    Note over Admin,OtherSvc: Tier-(a) upstream data (jo_*, mrd_*) is ingested by ram-reference-data's scheduled sync — never via these admin flows. These flows cover tier-(b) RAM-owned data only, and are DBA-via-SQL in MVP (D10).
